init_text:
What Are the Most Important Things Students Should Learn in School?

In your opinion, what are the most important things students should learn in school? What is the most important thing you have learned in school? How has this knowledge affected your life? How do you think it will help your success in the future?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The most important thing I have learned is that with literacy you can learn anything.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It also includes the ability to comprehend and interpret spoken or written information.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You can go on without knowing everything.

actions.name: text-delete
actions.text: ou can go on without knowing everything.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The more you practice critical thinking, the clearer your brain will become.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: There is a difference between being literate and educated.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A person can read and write but may not have the intellectual ability to understand or draw correct inference from that information.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: What is needed is the ability to think, not just memorize.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They don't want to pay if their children don't get good grades on standardized tests.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This is a big issue for educators.
